lass Solution:\n    def smallestEqual(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def smallestEqual(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        for i in range(len(nums)):\n            if i % 10 == nums[i]:\n                return i\n        return -1\n```\n\nThis code defines a method `smallestEqual` within the `Solution` class. It iterates through the list `nums`, checking if the current index `i` modulo 10 is equal to the value at `nums[i]`. If such an index is found, it returns that index. If no such index is found after checking all elements, it returns -1.", "estimated_date": 1635638400000}